The paper deals with a major challenge in machine learning, i.e., covariate shift, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science. The paper proposes a novel semi-supervised sparse filtering algorithm to address this problem. The paper's focus on machine learning algorithms and their application to real-world data sets suggests that it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
